about.summary: Automatically partitions data into evaluation bins, executes ecological niche models across a range of settings, and calculates a variety of evaluation statistics.  Current version only implements ENMs with Maxent (Phillips et al. 2006) or maxnet (Phillips et al. 2017).

Automatically partitions data into evaluation bins, executes ecological niche models across a range of settings, and calculates a variety of evaluation statistics.  Current version only implements ENMs with Maxent (Phillips et al. 2006) or maxnet (Phillips et al. 2017).

name: r-enmeval
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.0.4" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-enmeval
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ENMeval_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ENMeval/ENMeval_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 6d9f3c460fa7ab3131cede904fcb9280cf69f4fdd43f67115a3abcb8ed5b64d1

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dismo
    - r-doparallel
    - r-dosnow
    - r-dplyr
    - r-foreach
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glmnet
    - r-magrittr
    - r-maxnet
    - r-raster
    - r-sp
    - r-testthat
    - r-tidyr
    - r-rangemodelmetadata
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dismo
    - r-doparallel
    - r-dosnow
    - r-dplyr
    - r-foreach
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glmnet
    - r-magrittr
    - r-maxnet
    - r-raster
    - r-sp
    - r-testthat
    - r-tidyr
    - r-rangemodelmetadata

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ENMeval')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ENMeval')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=ENMeval
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: Automatically partitions data into evaluation bins, executes ecological niche models across a range of settings, and calculates a variety of evaluation statistics.  Current version only implements ENMs with Maxent (Phillips et al. 2006) or maxnet (Phillips et al. 2017).
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - colineroyaux
